thread.title: HS GOLF: Dunmore and Riverside post playoff wins in Small School; Valley View and Scranton Prep advance in Big School
thread.title_full: HS GOLF: Dunmore and Riverside post playoff wins in Small School; Valley View and Scranton Prep advance in Big School

author: STAFF REPORT
title: HS GOLF: Dunmore and Riverside post playoff wins in Small School; Valley View and Scranton Prep advance in Big School
text:
Sean Dempseyâ€™s individual win clinched a 5-4 victory for Dunmore against Lakeland in the first round of the Lackawanna League Small Division golf playoffs Wednesday at the Scranton Muni. 
Tom Dunda and Joe Weber swept three points in the first group for the Bucks. 
Tony Harding chipped in for eagle on No. 6 and birdied No. 7 to win two points for Lakeland. 
Dunmore will play Holy Cross in the semifinals on Friday at Scott Greens. 
Individuals: Tom Dunda (DUN) over Shane Novitsky, 2-up; Joe Weber (DUN) over James Eskra 5 and 3; Sean Dempsey (DUN) over Billy Lavelle, 1-up; Tony Harding (LAK) over Zach Pigga, 3 and 1; Connor Albino (LAK) over Christopher Murray, 2 and 1; Dominic DePietro (DUN) over John Wanas, 4 and 3. 
Better-ball: Dunda-Weber (DUN) over Novitsky-Eskra, 4 and 2; Lavelle-Harding (LAK) over Dempsey-Pigga, 2 and 1; Albino-Wanas (LAK) over Murray-DePietro, 2 and 1. 
Records: DUN 10-3, LAK 8-4-1. 
Riverside 5, Montrose 4 
At Pine Hills, Tyler Gaidula and Aaron Oustrich swept three points in the last group to lead Riverside in the first round of the Lackawanna League Small Division golf playoffs. 
Austin Smith and Paul Motsko had two wins for Montrose. 
Riverside will play Forest City in the semifinals on Friday at Memorial Links. 
Individuals: Austin Smith (MON) over Colin Quinn, 4 and 3; Evan Carrubba (RIV) over Jake Kelley, 2-up; Justin Copp (RIV) over Riley Brown, 1-up; Paul Motsko (MON) over Matt Torrisi, 2-up; Tyler Gaidula (RIV) over Collin Spellman, 5 and 4; Aaron Oustrich (RIV) over Isaac Walker, 3 and 2. 
Better-ball: Smith-Kelley (MON) over Quinn-Carrubba, 4 and 3; Brown-Motsko (MON) over Copp-Torrisi, 2-up; Gaidula-Oustrich (RIV) over Spellman-Walker, 3 and 2. 
Records: RIV 9-1-3, MON 7-5-1. 
Valley View 7, North Pocono 2 
At Scranton Muni, Hannah Yanoski and A.J. Ceccarelli each had two birdies and shot 3-under in better-ball to lead Valley View to a win in the first round of the Lackawanna League Big School Division playoffs. 
Ron Yanoski also had two birdies for the Cougars and Joe Tini birdied No. 10. 
Josh Toth birdied No. 14 for North Pocono. 
Valley View will play Abington Heights in the semifinals on Friday at Glen Oak Country Club. 
Individuals: Mitchell Mazza (VV) over Kyle Bowen, 2 and 1; Josh Toth (NP) over Ron Yanoski, 1-up; Jack Cerminaro (VV) and Nick Mokay (NP) split; Joe Tini (VV) over Pat Noone, 3 and 2; Hannah Yanoski (VV) over Jordan Tischler, 2 and 1; A.J. Ceccarelli (VV) over Zach Guse, 3 and 2. 
Better-ball: Mazza-R. Yanoski (VV) and Bowen-Toth (NP) split; Cerminaro-Tini (VV) over Mokay-Noone, 3 and 2; H. Yanoski-Ceccarelli (VV) over Tischler-Guse, 3 and 2. 
Records: VV 9-4-1, NP 8-5-1. 
Scranton Prep 9, Honesdale 0 
At the Scranton Muni, Sebastian Cimoch and Tyler Marchese shot 3-under par in better-ball to lead Scranton Prep in the first round of the Lackawanna League Big School Division playoffs. 
The Cavaliers will play Wallenpaupack in the semifinals on Friday at Woodloch Springs. 
Individuals: Sebastian Cimoch over Ian Langendoerfer, 2 and 1; Tyler Marchese over Konner Burke, 4 and 3; Jack Habeeb over Spencer Goyette, 4 and 3; Tom Keegan over Jack Rickard, 2 and 1; Marco Nieto over Luke Flederbach, 2 and 1; Frank Adamo over Steve Soden, 2-up. 
Better-ball: Cimoch-Marchese over Langendoerfer-Burke, 3 and 2; Habeeb-Keegan over Goyette-Rickard, 2 and 1; Nieto-Adamo over Flederbach-Soden, 2 and 1. 
Records: SP 11-2-1, HON 6-8.
